The paper presents a data-driven optimal control framework that uses probabilistic representation of learned dynamics model to find iterative feedback control laws without parameterization. This involves solving optimization problems under uncertainty, which is a common theme in machine learning and robotics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.RO (Robotics), cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.SD (Software Engineering).
